  "description": [
    "THE MIAMI TIMESThe Peoples Newspaper PAGE 6 RadioTV Commentary ChicagoA N P Congress man William L Dawson DHJL apparently thought he was mak ing a campaign speech last Wednesday night as he spoke fol lowing a floor fight on the em battled civil rights issue as the Democratic National convention here The Illinois Democrat elaborat ed upon the fanm program touch ed the foreign policy issues blast ed the Republican party but pass ed very little comment upon the allimportant civil rights issue which had been thrashed out shortly before he took the floor The moderately weak platform on civil rights received practically no comment form the Illinois re presentative as Negro audiences looking in on television awaited his reaction on the plank However anallout effort by the northern liberals to amend the language of the civil rights plank cannot be overlooked without giving the minority delegations an E for effort The battle of the extremists ended up with a compromise civil rights plank just as it always has By virtue of Negro action the Democratic party will ultimately have to recognize that it cannot continue as they have in the past to have the Negro and the South too"
  ],
